the establishment of the Federation of Saint Kitts and Nevis in 1983. The Federation of Saint Kitts and Nevis is a sovereign state and a Commonwealth realm, with the British monarch as head of state. The Federation comprises two main islands, Saint Kitts and Nevis, and several smaller islands. The capital city is Basseterre on the island of Saint Kitts. The Federation is a member of the Caribbean Community (CARICOM), the Organisation of Eastern Caribbean States (OECS), the Commonwealth of Nations, and the United Nations. The official language is English.

Saint Kitts and Nevis is a member of the Commonwealth of Nations, the Organisation of Eastern Caribbean States, the Caribbean Community, the United Nations, and the World Trade Organization. The country is a founding member of the Organisation of American States and the Caribbean Community.
